 on connects students and community members with local farms\, food systems
 \, and hands-on learning experiences. A coalition of farm groups work toge
 ther to share the importance of agriculture and farming in Marin County. F
 ind the Diggin' Education table at Farm Day for some giveaways and seasona
 l produce samples! Don't forget to check out the AIM Thursday Farmers Mark
 et afterwards to experience out local food system in action. This free eve
 nt is open to the public! Teachers \\(K - 6th grade\\) can  pre-register t
 he classes to receive a swag bag with agricultural resources for your clas
 sroom and raffle ticket entry to win prizes.
