BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bottle Baby Breakfast Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260326T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260326T160000
UID:2603122aL3axJKAUOGzppLYt5gOQ
DESCRIPTION:**Tiny Hooves\, Big Hearts: Our Ongoing Rescue Mission**\n\n**
 At Goatlandia\, our mission is simple: to give love\, safety\, and a secon
 d chance to animals who need it most.**\n\n**We were recently called to re
 scue three baby goats. These tiny babies are now safe at Goatlandia\, and 
 they need bottle feeding several times a day to stay healthy and thrive.**
 \n\n**That’s Where You Come In: The Bottle Baby Breakfast Club**\n\n**St
 arting March 6th\, join us for a heartwarming hour on the farm\, bottle-fe
 eding and cuddling our newest rescues while supporting their care.**\n\n**
 Your $250 donation (covers milk and supplies for weeks of feedings) includ
 es admission for up to four guests for a private\, unforgettable visit to 
 Goatlandia.**\n\n**Come share the love\, feel the magic\, and help us give
  these little ones the future they deserve.**
LOCATION:Goatlandia
URL:https://www.goatlandia.org/bottle-babies-breakfast-club
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Alibi Book Club: "The Lion Women of Tehran" by Marjan Kamali
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260326T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260326T190000
UID:260311n_e8yco2mkym_BfhpLkDGA
DESCRIPTION:We are closing out Women's History Month with the NYT bestsell
 ing and NPR Best Book of the Year "The Lion Women of Tehran" by Marjan Kam
 ali.\n\nNOTE: When I chose this book a few months ago\, I didn't have any 
 idea of what was going to happen in regards to Iran\, and especially the g
 irls' school. Rather than change the book\, I think we should read and lea
 rn. Thank you\, and hope to see you there.\n\n"Evocative...and a powerful 
 portrait of friendship\, feminism\, and political activism" -- People\n\n"
 Kamali writes beautifully and passionately about friendship\, love\, youth
 \, conflict\, aging and the challenges of sustaining meaningful relationsh
 ips amid high-stakes Iranian politics. The novel is full of atmosphere\, h
 istory\, great food and two unforgettable heroines...\\[who\\] will endear
  and intrigue readers from the opening scenes to the last page - a must-re
 ad." --NPR\n\nIn 1950s Tehran\, seven-year-old Ellie lives in grand comfor
 t until the untimely death of her father\, forcing Ellie and her mother to
  move to a tiny home downtown. Lonely and bearing the brunt of her mother'
 s endless grievances\, Ellie dreams for a friend to alleviate her isolatio
 n.\n\nLuckily\, on the first day of school\, she meets Homa\, a kind girl 
 with a brave and irrepressible spirit. Together\, the two girls play games
 \, learn to cook in the stone kitchen of Homa's warm home\, wander through
  the colorful stalls of the Grand Bazaar\, and share their ambitions of be
 coming "lion women."\n\nBut their happiness is disrupted when Ellie and he
 r mother are afforded the opportunity to return to their previous bourgeoi
 s life. Now a popular student at the best girls' high school in Iran\, Ell
 ie's memories of Homa begin to fade. Years later\, however\, her sudden re
 appearance in Ellie's privileged world alters the course of both of their 
 lives.\n\nTogether\, the two young women come of age and pursue their own 
 goals for meaningful futures. But as the political turmoil in Iran builds 
 to a breaking point\, one earth-shattering betrayal will have enormous con
 sequences.\n\n"Reminiscent of The Kite Runner and My Brilliant Friend\, Th
 e Lion Women of Tehran is a mesmerizing tale" \\( BookPage\\) of love and 
 courage\, and a sweeping exploration of how profoundly we are shaped by th
 ose we meet when we are young."\n\nBooks are available in the shop\, onlin
 e and ebooks: bookshop.org/shop/alibibookshop and audio: libro.fm/alibiboo
 kshop
LOCATION:Alibi Bookshop
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/1606870150562019
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Stories from the Smithsonian Center for Folklife
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260326T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260326T183000
UID:2603099-V68npIMkOglv7pB6hfJQ
DESCRIPTION:Oral Histories as Research and Cultural Democracy\n\nWhy do we
  tell our stories? Why listen to\, record\, archive\, and share the memori
 es of others? As part of the Making History\, Making Change Lecture Series
 \, Dr. Rebecca Fenton\, curator at the Smithsonian Center for Folklife and
  Cultural Heritage\, will explore how oral histories bring rich texture to
  our understanding of past events and traditions. Lifting up the narrators
 ' participation in cultural life\, oral histories reveal the many ways tha
 t all kinds of people shape their communities. For those inspired to recor
 d an oral history interview\, Dr. Fenton will also share resources and too
 ls for getting started in your family and community.\n\nThe Making History
 \, Making Change Lecture Series is a national collaboration between the Sm
 ithsonian and 25 Smithsonian Affiliate organizations\, featuring expert-le
 d talks that explore the people\, moments\, and ideals that have shaped—
 and continue to shape—the American experience.\n\nThe Making History\, M
 aking Change Lecture Series is organized by Smithsonian Affiliations as pa
 rt of the Smithsonian’s Our Shared Future: 250. It is supported in part 
 by the Dreier Family\, Johanna and Ken Kim Family\, Vaishali Shah Chadha a
 nd Family\, and Michael Vu & Meridel Bulle-Vu.\n\nLearn more: https://aff
 iliations.si.edu/making-history-making-change
LOCATION:Museums of Sonoma County
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/stories-from-the-smiths
 onian-center-for-folklife/18290426/2026-03-26T17
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:March Month of Flowers Challenge
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260326T000000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260326T120000
UID:260306mAFH4NM74U6rINzG2zD7SQ
DESCRIPTION:Starting March 1st begins the "March Month of Flowers Challeng
 e" \\(online\\). \n\nYou'll receive a list of prompts for every day in Mar
 ch. \n\nCreate an art piece related to the prompt.\n\nShare in our privat
 e Facebook group.\n\nBe inspired and give inspiration to others.\n\nOnly $
 5\, so everyone can join and share in this creative adventure!\n\nMarch Mo
 nth of Flowers Challenge is here to give you a creative outlet\, some st
 ructure\, and respite from your brain. \n\nWhen you pick up a brush\, pen
 \, or pencil \\(thread\, clay\, fabric…\\)\, your brain gets a rest and 
 becomes more alive and flexible. The world around you becomes more alive\
 ; you pick up on shades\, details\, and patterns all around you. Your in
 tuition gets stronger. And fear lessens\, anxiety fades\, and curiosity gr
 ows. You stop worrying about making mistakes\, and instead\, you find the
  freedom to simply create
URL:https://www.taradickinson.com/project-page/workshops
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
