BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Jack London & the Captains Who Inspired Him
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260327T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260327T183000
UID:260216MG-W9Y1pg0KVT7LmiAC5Cg
DESCRIPTION:This is the first of a series of lectures presented by Jack Lo
 ndon Park Partners and the Jack London Society\, honoring the 150th annive
 rsary of Jack London’s birth.  A compelling lineup of speakers and acti
 vities celebrating Jack London’s legacy will be offered at the park thro
 ughout 2026.  For information on upcoming anniversary events\, visit jack
 londonpark.com/150th-birthday/.\n\nThe Jack London Society is an internati
 onal non-profit organization that promotes study of the life and work of J
 ack London.  Learn more at jacklondonsociety.org/.\n\nBefore Jack London 
 captained his own boats as an oyster pirate and bestselling author\, he wa
 s inspired by the captains of his time: Joshua Slocum\, the first person 
 to sail solo around the world\; William T. Shorey\, the whaling captain k
 nown as the Black Ahab whose home port was Oakland\; and Alexander McLean\
 , an inspiration for Wolf Larsen\, the sadistic captain who animates the d
 ark side of London’s novel\, The Sea-Wolf.\n\nJoin Aleta George in the 
 House of Happy Walls Museum at Jack London State Historic Park to learn ab
 out the captains who inspired London and how they found their way into his
  imagination.\n\nAbout the speaker: Aleta George writes about the nature\,
  history\, and culture of California. Her work has appeared in Smithsonia
 n\, the Los Angeles Times\, Bay Nature\, Estuary News\, and Latitude 3
 8. She is the award-winning author of “Ina Coolbrith: The Bittersweet S
 ong of California’s First Poet Laureate” \\(one of Jack’s mentors\\)
  and is working on a biography about London’s formative\, lifelong relat
 ionship with San Francisco Bay.
LOCATION:Jack London State Historic Park
URL:https://jacklondonpark.com/events/jl-speaker-series-aleta-george/ 
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Adult Gymnastics Class
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260327T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260327T183000
UID:260214rodwdr14S0mzCoC7QNh__w
DESCRIPTION:We’re offering Adult Gymnastics Classes for the 18\\+ crowd!
 \n\nAdult Gymnastics classes occur every Tuesday 5:00 PM to 6:30 PM & Fri
 day from 6:30 PM to 8:00 PM.\n\n$20 per person\, OR pay for a whole 8-we
 ek session in advance through our site. You can attend on Tuesday\, Friday
 \, or both!\n\nPlease bring the class fee in cash at the time of arrival. 
 This can be a DROP IN\, so there is no need to sign up online before comin
 g!\n\nIf you’ve ever wanted to try out gymnastics or get back into it in
  adulthood\, now is your chance! During our adult classes\, open to all ge
 nders\, our coaches will move at the pace of each student\, helping them a
 chieve goals they set for themselves. No experience is necessary to be i
 nvolved in this class\, so this is a great opportunity to learn the basics
  and get some exercise\, no matter what age you are! Try out our trampolin
 e\, bars\, beam\, and other gym equipment in a safe and supportive environ
 ment. You can build strength and increase your range of motion while havin
 g fun like you’re a kid again.\n\nAsk our coaches what you can work on b
 etween classes\, and they’ll help personalize your training!\n\nPlease w
 ear something comfortable and keep long hair tied back. Skirts and restric
 tive clothing are not recommended. You must remove your shoes before going
  onto the mat or using equipment. Please let us know if you have any physi
 cal limitations or health conditions that may interfere with doing certain
  motions. We recommend bringing a water bottle.\n\nYou can email us for mo
 re info or join our mailing list at: info@sonomagymnasticsacademy.com
LOCATION:Sonoma Gymnastics Academy
URL:https://sonomagymnasticsacademy.com/home/adult-gymnastics-night/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
