DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T163000
UID:260325WdilkfvjXUiVw87QP1lWQg
DESCRIPTION:Learn how to save a life!\n\nFocusing on recognizing and treat
 ing life-threatening situations in the critical minutes before 911 arrives
 \, we will cover adult and infant CPR\, AED use\, handling choking as well
  as what to do in cases of severe bleeding\, sudden illness\, heart attack
 \, stroke and more.\n\nFocusing on recognizing and treating life-threateni
 ng situations in the critical minutes before 911 arrives\, we will cover a
 dult and infant CPR\, AED use and handling choking\, as well as what to do
  in cases of severe bleeding\, sudden illness\, heart attack\, stroke and 
 more. We'll be using modern manikins and equipment in a small-group settin
 g\, and answering questions along the way.\n\nYour American Red Cross cert
 ificate will be valid for 2 years.\n\n\\(This community class event is hel
 d at a branch of Sonoma County Library. We thank them for their hospitalit
 y. They have requested that we mention that this program is neither sponso
 red by nor affiliated with the Sonoma County Library. Done!\\)\n\nPlease g
 et in touch with any questions!
LOCATION:Healdsburg Library
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/american-red-cross-adul
 t-and-pediatric-first-aid-cpr-aed-class-blended/18179187/2026-03-28T14
