BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:No Kings 3: Rally\, Food Drive & March
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T120000
UID:260320-QbVQvd3h0mpk-58VSEdqw
DESCRIPTION:Across the country\, Americans are asking hard questions about
  the direction of our democracy.\n\nWhen federal immigration enforcement a
 ctions expand with limited oversight… When journalists face arrest or in
 timidation while doing their jobs… When transparency around high-profile
  investigations raises public concern… When families feel the squeeze of
  rising costs and economic uncertainty…\n\nIt forces us to ask: Who hold
 s power accountable?\n\nThe founders rejected monarchy for a reason. They 
 built a system designed to prevent concentrated\, unchecked authority. “
 No Kings” is not a slogan — it is a reminder that in America\, power f
 lows from the people\, and leaders are accountable to the Constitution.\n\
 nOn March 28\, Vallejo joins millions nationwide for the third No Kings Da
 y of Action.\n\nJoin us for:\n\n• Guest speakers\n\n• Live music\n\n
 • A community march\n\n• A food drive in partnership with the Food Ban
 k of Contra Costa and Solano\n\nLast time\, more than 1\,200 neighbors sto
 od together. This time\, we aim to grow even stronger.\n\nThis is about de
 fending democratic norms\, protecting a free press\, demanding transparenc
 y\, and ensuring that the government serves the people — not the other w
 ay around.\n\nBring a friend. Bring your voice. Bring shelf-stable food 
  \\(no glass\\) to support local families.\n\nThere are no kings here.
LOCATION:Unity Plaza – JFK Library | Vallejo
URL:https://www.mobilize.us/mobilize/event/914424/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Social Contractors: Rock & Resist @ The Block!
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T210000
UID:260319svYbNvFspkqLqbYuFuouTw
DESCRIPTION:“….Get ready for the super-entertaining sounds of local ba
 nd The Social Contractors. They totally rock\, in all the right ways…”
  - Argus-Courier\n\nJoin us on the evening of the "No Kings" march as we "
 rock and resist" at The Block from 6-9PM!\n\nWe'll be performing the live 
 band version of our recently released single\; "Tiniest Human"\, a "rock o
 de to the orange one"\, along with other politically themed tunes plus cla
 ssic hits from The Beatles\, The Police\, Jimi Hendrix\, The Doors\, Pink 
 Floyd\, Tears for Fears\, Steely Dan\, Tom Petty\, U2\, and more!\n\nThe l
 ineup for this show will be band founder\, Jason E. Davies \\(lead and rhy
 thm guitar/vocals/songwriting\\)\, Travis Thayer \\(sax/keys/vocals\\)\, A
 lex Fabian-Davies \\(bass\\)\, and special guest artist Scott McKenzie on 
 drums!\n\nCome "rock and resist" with us\, at one of Petaluma's best outdo
 or music\, food\, and beverage venues!
LOCATION:The Block
URL:https://www.theblockpetaluma.com
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
