BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Country Line Dancing Night ft. Dustin Saylor & The Stowaways
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T190000
UID:260228LvBHmzcMxkSUTQW7Zw_PNA
DESCRIPTION:**Date:** Saturday\, March 28\, 2026\n\n**Time:** Doors 6 PM 
 | Lessons 7-8 PM | Live music throughout the night\n\n**Tickets:** $20 Adv
 ance | $25 Door | Coyote Sonoma Members Receive $5 Off\n\nJoin us for line
  dancing lessons from Grapevine Dance! Plus live music from Dustin Saylor 
 & The Stowaways.\n\nAbout Dustin Saylor:\n\nDustin Saylor\, a Northern Cal
 ifornia-born country singer-songwriter\, has made a name for himself as th
 e #1 Country/Folk artist in the San Francisco Bay Area. His musical journe
 y began in childhood\, first at the piano and later as a guitarist and sin
 ger for his high school youth group and local church. Despite early challe
 nges\, including a devastating American Idol rejection in 2009\, Saylor ha
 d a transformative moment on his long drive home\, realizing that true suc
 cess required full commitment. Embracing his calling\, he quit bartending\
 , pursued a music degree at Sonoma State University\, and became a full-ti
 me musician. Over the years\, he has performed alongside artists like Tyle
 r Rich\, Chase Rice\, and Daughtry\, with his sound often compared to Thom
 as Rhett and Chris Stapleton. His songwriting is deeply personal\, shaped 
 by his early experiences of adoption and the contrasting struggles and joy
 s of his life. Through his music\, Saylor seeks to inspire\, heal\, and cr
 eate a space where people can connect beyond labels. Committed to his craf
 t\, he remains "all in\," determined to sing and play music for the rest o
 f his life.
LOCATION:Coyote Sonoma
URL:https://shop.coyotesonoma.com/country-line-dancing-with-dustin-saylor-
 -the-stowaways-328-p216.aspx
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Park Rx—Intermediate Hiking for Fitness
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T130000
UID:260227ZlUaa05XXUGArq6Z1f7VRg
DESCRIPTION:If you have previously completed the Beginner Hiking f
 or Fitness Program\, or can hike a little more than 4 miles wi
 th at least 1\,000 ft of elevation\, this hiking series is for
  you! The program leaders will guide you on 8 weekly hikes wit
 h the challenge increasing each week. Leaders will have group di
 scussions about gear\, hydration\, hiking poles\, first aid and p
 acing\, etc. The group's final hike aims for Bald Mountain\, whe
 re hikers can enjoy stunning vistas.\n\nThe following is a list 
 of possible routes specifically selected for this hiking series: 
 \n\n1) Sat 3/7 — Creekside + Waterfall loop\, 3.6 miles\, 750
  ft elevation \\[meet @ White Barn\\] 2) Sat 3/14 – Vista Tra
 il loop\, 3.4 miles\, 830 ft elevation \\[meet @ White Barn\\] 3
 ) Sat 3/21 – Goodspeed to Nattkemper bench\, 3.8 miles\, 1\,24
 0 ft elevation \\[meet @ Goodspeed lot\\] 4) Sat 3/28 – Hillsi
 de to Neptune table + Meadow\, 4.4 miles\, 970 ft elevation \\[
 meet @ White Barn\\] 5) Sat 4/4 – Hillside + Vista Trail loop
 \, 3.6 miles\, 1\,070 ft elevation \\[meet @ White Barn\\] 6) Sa
 t 4/11 – False Lake Meadow & Lake Ilsanjo loop in Trionne-Ann
 adel SP\, 6.1 miles\, 670 ft elevation \\[meet @ Annadel's Cobbl
 estone Trailhead\\] 7) Sat 4/18 – Fern Lake + Orchard loop in
  SDC/Jack London SHP\, 5.5 miles\, 1\,460 ft elevation \\[meet @
  Walnut & North St inside SDC\; park on Grove St\\] 8) Sat 4/2
 5 – Bald Mtn summit (w/optional Headwaters detour\, 5.8 miles)\
 , 5.1 miles\, 1\,670 ft elevation \\[meet @ White Barn\\]\n\nPlea
 se note these routes are subject to change based on the group 
 and weather. Wear appropriate footwear for rocky or slippery trai
 ls\, and layers. Bring water\, and if desired\, a snack. The gr
 oup will be limited to 35 participants. \n\nThe hiking series co
 sts $80 (plus a $10 parking fee per visit. Note that the Sugar
 loaf Annual Pass is $59 and valid at Sugarloaf and Jack London
  SHP)\, or free-of-cost for participants with a January 2025 or
  newer Park Rx from a Sonoma County Medical Provider.  The num
 ber of available Park Rx tickets is limited\; please have your 
 Rx ready at the time of sign up.
LOCATION:Sugarloaf Ridge State Park
URL:https://sec.regfox.com/inthffspring26
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Callie Watts
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T000000
UID:260227BtuM1Wdc3ESHfKvadjuPiQ
DESCRIPTION:Callie Watts is a singer/songwriter from Northern California w
 ho was raised on classical music\, The Beatles and The Beach Boys before d
 iscovering Joni Mitchell\, Elton John\, Stevie Wonder\, Paul Simon\, Billy
  Joel\, Carole King\, and all the great writers of the ’60s and 70’s w
 ho have influenced her sound and writing style. After graduating high scho
 ol\, Callie began playing and performing solo\, as well as in local and ba
 y area bands of different genres. She’s played blues with Eric Lindell a
 nd the Reds\, funky soul with Phatty\, and jazz/swing with Savoy Swingers 
 along with many other various projects. Callie has taken turns throughout 
 her career as a keyboardist\, guitarist\, writer\, and lead/backing vocali
 st\, and she’s currently a member of the dynamic Sonoma County funk rock
  band Burrows and Dilbeck\, having joined in 2010 as part of the former ba
 nd Frobeck. Over time\, she’s had the honor of opening for acts such as 
 Bootsy Collins\, Elvin Bishop\, Huey Lewis and The News\, War\, Ozomatli\,
  Bill Champlin\, Booker T\, and the B52s. Callie continues to perform freq
 uently as an acoustic solo artist\, focusing on developing a core audience
  and a buzz for her original material. Come hang out and listen at venues 
 such as Aroma Roasters\, Rincon Valley Tap Room and Bottle Shop\, and Hopm
 onk Tavern.
LOCATION:4th Street cellars
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107647208?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Glass Menagerie
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T213000
UID:2602276wQTocZVhkmmHQKXVlBK7A
DESCRIPTION:The 2026 Season at Curtain Call Theatre starts off with **The 
 Glass Menagerie**\, the play that made Tennessee Williams famous.\n\nHave 
 You Ever Felt Stuck Between Your Dreams and Reality? This Play Gets It.\n\
 nImagine being trapped in a tiny apartment during the Great Depression —
  no money\, no way out\, just a family clinging to hopes that may never co
 me true. That's exactly what The Glass Menagerie is about.\n\nWritten by T
 ennessee Williams — one of America's greatest playwrights — this story
  follows a restless son\, an overbearing mom\, and a painfully shy daughte
 r as they each chase dreams that feel just out of reach. It's emotional\, 
 poetic\, and honestly… kind of hits different when you think about your 
 own life.\n\nThis iconic play is literally studied in classrooms worldwide
 \, so seeing it live is like watching your textbook come to life — excep
 t way more powerful.\n\n📅 March 13–29\, 2026\n\n📍 20347 Hwy 116\, 
 Monte Rio\, CA\n\n🎟️ Grab your tickets at russianriverhall.com or cal
 l (707) 387-5072\n\nThe Glass Menagerie by Tennessee Williams is directed 
 by Michael Tabib.\n\nShowing at the Russian River Hall in Monte Rio\, CA f
 rom March 13-29\, 2026.\n\nProgram was made possible\, in part\, with fund
 s from Creative Sonoma and the California Arts Council (CAC).\n\nBy specia
 l arrangement with Dramatists Play Services\, Inc.
LOCATION:Curtain Call Theatre
URL:https://www.russianriverhall.com/2026/02/18/march-13-29-the-glass-mena
 gerie/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"You're My Neighbor" Art Exhibit
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T180000
UID:2602275MpzfOacG0K_qQo1IcIssw
DESCRIPTION:Come out to Point Reyes and celebrate neighbors!   \n\nFrom 
 mooing cows and soaring birds to friendly faces down the road\, Cedars art
 ists take a joyful look at their Marin County neighborhood. This exhibitio
 n explores all the things that make their corner of the world special—op
 en fields\, wild creatures\, familiar people\, and the everyday moments in
  between. Through colorful\, thoughtful\, and imaginative works\, “You
 ’re My Neighbor” celebrates the beauty of living side by side and shar
 ing a place we call home.\n\n​Cedars “You’re My Neighbor!” art exh
 ibition runs from March 3 through April 12\, 2026
LOCATION:Toby's Feed Barn
URL:https://www.cedarslife.org/events
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
