BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Workshop: Integrating watercolor with Chinese ink and oil pastel w
 ith Dr. QinQin Liu
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T123000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T153000
UID:2603257L5gzhtbuUOpqyuFZkNnTQ
DESCRIPTION:Limited to 12 studentsSaturday March 28\, 2026 12:30pm - 3:30p
 mTickets: $90 Non-Members\\*$80 Members and Students\\*\n\n\\(\\*Class mat
 erials are not included. Required materials list is detailed below.\\) \n\
 nIn this lively workshop\, Dr. Liu will teach students a unique form of wa
 tercolor integration with Chinese ink and oil pastel. Students will also l
 earn design\, composition\, shape\, line\, point\, value and color by pain
 ting natural objects. By using Chinese brush stroke and wet-on-wet techniq
 ues\, participants will explore the power of positive and negative paintin
 gs. They will also experiment with watercolor expression and abstraction w
 ith splashing\, dripping\, and Chinese calligraphy painting.  \n\nThe work
 shop will begin with an instructor demo\, followed by individual instructi
 on and group discussion. \n\nDr. Qinqin Liu has taught watercolor workshop
 s since 2017 at Yosemite National Park\, Sitka Art and Ecology Center\, an
 d Chalk Hill Art Residency in California and Oregon Coast. She has practic
 ed ink painting and calligraphy in China since 1974. When she came to the 
 U.S.\, she studied with award-winning watercolorists Frank Webb and Profes
 sor Cheng-Khee Chee.  \n\nRequired Materials List: \n\nSketchbook \\(at le
 ast 5"x 8"\\)\n\nWatercolor paper \\(Arches Cold press 140lb at least two 
 sheets 11x15\\)\n\n2 B and 6B pencils  \n\nPalette for color mixing \\(e.g
 . a recycled egg plastic container\\)\n\nWatercolor brushes \\(Princeton b
 rand is good\\): Rounds sizes 6 and 10 or 12\; Flats sizes 1 &frac12\;&rdq
 uo\; and larger\n\nWatercolor paints: 3 primary colors \\(e.g.\, Ultramari
 ne Blue\, Azo Yellow\, and Cadmium Red or rose madder\\)\, optional sap gr
 een\, and any of your favorite colors.\n\nTwo water containers \\(e.g.\, t
 wo empty yogurt containers\\).\n\nPaper clamps\, a water spray bottle\, sp
 onges\, and a paper towel.\n\nMasking tapes and boards to secure the water
 color papers during the painting.\n\nMr. Clean Erasers \\(cleaning pads th
 at you can buy in Walmart or other stores\\).\n\nOptional: masks\; your fa
 vorite natural objects and drawings.\n\nMaterials Provided by Instructor:\
 n\nChinese ink and brush as well as oil pastels for class demo and limited
  uses.\n\nTissue paper\, plastic wraps\, and natural objects such as sunfl
 owers \n\nWatercolor paintings and sketch examples as well as class handou
 ts.  
LOCATION:Petaluma Arts Center
URL:https://mynorthbaytickets.ticketsauce.com/e/workshop-integrating-water
 color-with-chinese-ink-a?aff=cityspark
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
