BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Local Author Read Aloud: Bubbles with Andre Morrow
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T120000
UID:260318tNFifUNo_E6f5s8Qp2aJQA
DESCRIPTION:Join us on Sunday\, March 29th\, from 11am-12pm\, for a fun ch
 ildren’s read-aloud of Bubbles by local author André Morrow! All are we
 lcome to join us in reading and celebrating this musical tale. We’ll be 
 featuring live children’s songs\, snacks\, and an engaging storytime.  
 “Bubbles” is a whimsical story that teaches young readers to appreciat
 e all the wonderful little things in life\, like playing with pets and fam
 ily\, blowing bubbles\, and enjoying the outdoors. The story highlights gr
 atitude in a playful and educational way!\n\nRead more about the precious 
 story of how Bubbles came to be\, quoted directly from the author:\n\n " 
 Bubbles is a song\, video and children's book. The "Bubbles" project began
  during a visit with some of my grandkids\, Hadley Dickson\, James Dickson
 \, and Danica Dickson. Most of our visits include music time and taking a 
 whack at writing songs together. On this particular visit\, we'd just fini
 shed an enthusiastic adventure making bubbles in the backyard. Afterward\,
  during music time\, I asked them what they wanted to write about and one 
 of them yelled out "Bubbles". And the song was born. Months later\, my mus
 ic partner David J. Michalak and I began producing the song to add to our 
 collection of music. My cousins\, Sophia Bass and Catherine Bass\, sisters
 \, both wonderful artists\, agreed to assist us with the project. Catherin
 e is an amazing painter and Sophia's voice is incomparable. They are the d
 aughters of my cousin Reggie Bass who was my great friend and music partne
 r of my youth. So together we all created the Bubbles book\, song\, and vi
 deo. We hope you enjoy it! The song can be found on all major music platfo
 rms using the artist's name Morrow Michalak. The video can be found at mor
 rowmichalak.com/bubbles. Thanks to Barb Schacht\, who heard an early rendi
 tion of the song and suggested it would make a terrific kid's book. ”\n\
 nWishing you Butterflies\, Sunshine\, and Rainbows\, André \\(Papi\\) Mor
 row
LOCATION:Usher Gallery
URL:https://ushergallerypetaluma.com/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
