BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:GLYPH  - Art Exhibition
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T150000
UID:2603105dDpdJonTkujN9evBPWxew
DESCRIPTION:Glyph will be on view through May 3. Personal Space is open Su
 ndays 11 a.m. to 3 p.m. and by appointment.\n\nBig news! Personal Space is
  back from our \\(much needed\\) hiatus. Join us next Sunday\, March 15 \
 \(2-5pm\\) for the opening of  Glyph. This is our first opening since Vil
 lage opened up next door\, and it’s sure to be a party!\n\nFeaturing thi
 rteen artists from the Bay Area and beyond\, Glyph embraces a liminal spac
 e which allows subconscious connections to reign and centers gut feeling a
 s a source of poetry\, mystery\, and magic. Collectively\, these artists d
 raw from an enigmatic lexicon of symbols\, favoring inscrutable familiarit
 y over anything known or quantified. This intuitive language manifests thr
 ough a varied approach to material translation that underscores\, and cele
 brates\, our innate ability to understand things deeply without having to 
 define them in words.\n\nGlyph features works by:\n\nSadie Buckner \n\nLu
 is Estrada \n\nRochele Gomez \n\nKainoa Gruspe \n\nLéonie Guyer \n\nK
 lea McKenna\n\nMitzi Pederson \n\nBen Peterson \n\nJ Pendleton\n\nRobert
  Smithson \n\nEmma Spertus \n\nHenna Vainio \n\nRichard Zimmerman \n\n
 See link for details and artist bios.
LOCATION:Personal Space
URL:https://personalspace.space/exhibitions/glyph
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
