SUMMARY:March Month of Flowers Challenge
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T000000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T120000
UID:2603068N9wJKHKcUyv1QRdGqynow
DESCRIPTION:Starting March 1st begins the "March Month of Flowers Challeng
 e" \\(online\\). \n\nYou'll receive a list of prompts for every day in Mar
 ch. \n\nCreate an art piece related to the prompt.\n\nShare in our privat
 e Facebook group.\n\nBe inspired and give inspiration to others.\n\nOnly $
 5\, so everyone can join and share in this creative adventure!\n\nMarch Mo
 nth of Flowers Challenge is here to give you a creative outlet\, some st
 ructure\, and respite from your brain. \n\nWhen you pick up a brush\, pen
 \, or pencil \\(thread\, clay\, fabric…\\)\, your brain gets a rest and 
 becomes more alive and flexible. The world around you becomes more alive\
 ; you pick up on shades\, details\, and patterns all around you. Your in
 tuition gets stronger. And fear lessens\, anxiety fades\, and curiosity gr
 ows. You stop worrying about making mistakes\, and instead\, you find the
  freedom to simply create
URL:https://www.taradickinson.com/project-page/workshops
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Hanging with Horses: Middle School
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T103000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T120000
UID:260305Uzm7-_BUcE67mkHBtsRC0Q
DESCRIPTION:Middle school can be… a lot. Friendships changing. Siblings.
  Academic stress. Anxious moments. Parents. You know. Horses are amazing f
 riends\, guides\, listeners\, and healers. They really know about relation
 ships. AND they are experts at stress management. Hanging with Horses: Mid
 dle School is a three-week group meeting consecutively on Sundays\, March 
 15-29\, 10:30 AM\, on a beautiful old cattle ranch between Novato and Peta
 luma. If you join **Hanging with Horses**\, you will have a blast and beco
 me a part of a wonderful herd (horses and humans.) You might also...\n\nTr
 y grounding and relaxation tools that actually help.\n\nBuild confidence a
 nd leadership—just by being yourself.\n\nLearn to speak horse while cari
 ng for the herd.\n\nYou don’t have to talk if you’re not ready. You do
 n’t have to be “good with people.” You don’t need any horse experi
 ence.\n\nJust come as you are. The horses will meet you there 🐎✨\n\nT
 hrough unpressured time “hanging with horses\,” guided group conversat
 ions\, and hands-on experiences\, participants will learn to:\n\nUnderstan
 d what stress and anxiety feel like in their own bodies\n\nBuild healthier
  friendships and boundaries\n\nDevelop emotional awareness and leadership 
 skills\n\nPractice grounding and calming tools they can use anywhere\n\nGa
 in confidence by tuning into themselves and their environment\n\nHorses na
 turally reflect emotions and stress levels\, giving kids a powerful (and n
 on-judgmental) way to learn about themselves and others.\n\n🐎**NEIGH**:
  You can schedule a call to speak with the director of Heart & Mind Equine
  to learn more and see if this group is a good option for your family. Sch
 edule here.\n\nScholarships are available. Please reach out or schedule a 
 call to request- HeartMindEquine@gmail.com\n\nLearn more and register here
 : https://hwhorses-middle-school.eventbrite.com
LOCATION:Heart & Mind Equine Horse Rescue
URL:https://hwhorses-middle-school.eventbrite.com
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"Rent School Edition"- Musical
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T170000
UID:2603050a6vslOrpEq0jHL9LK1YLQ
DESCRIPTION:Set in the East Village of New York City\, Rent School Edition
  is about falling in love\, finding your voice and living for today. Winne
 r of the Tony Award for Best Musical and the Pulitzer Prize for Drama\, it
  has become a pop cultural phenomenon with songs that rock and a story tha
 t resonates with audiences of all ages.\n\nBased loosely on Puccini’s La
  Boheme\, Rent School Edition follows a year in the life of a group of imp
 overished young artists and musicians struggling to survive and create in 
 New York’s Lower East Side\, under the shadow of HIV/AIDS. The physical 
 and emotional complications of the disease pervade the lives of Roger\, Mi
 mi\, Tom and Angel. Maureen deals with her chronic infidelity through perf
 ormance art\; her partner\, Joanne\, wonders if their relationship is wort
 h the trouble. Benny has sold out his Bohemian ideals in exchange for a he
 fty income and is on the outs with his former friends. Mark\, an aspiring 
 filmmaker\, feels like an outsider to life in general. How these young boh
 emians negotiate their dreams\, loves and conflicts provides the narrative
  thread to this groundbreaking musical.\n\nCredits\n\nBook\, Music\, and L
 yrics by Jonathan Larson\n\nDirected by Kele Gasparini\n\nEnjoy our LIVE P
 it Orchestra\n\nTickets: GoFan.CO \n\nhttps://gofan.co/app/school/CA23048
 \n\nSuggested Audience Age 13\\+\n\nContent Warnings\n\nAdult Themes\, Dri
 nking\, Drugs & Smoking\, Mild Language
LOCATION:San Marin High - Emily Gates Performing Arts Center
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/rent-school-edition-mus
 ical/18179688/2026-03-29T14
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sky Ranch Gallery presents Mary McDougall as the March Featured Ar
 tist
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T140000
UID:260228uPIpINep10-g3ObUrZZB3A
DESCRIPTION:Homeward Bound 12x12 acrylic\n\nMary McDougall is a retired po
 tter turned painter. As a painter her first love is landscapes\, as she sa
 ys\, “It is all about Mother Earth”. Living in the midst of such beaut
 y\, her paintings often depict the quiet serenity and explosive color of t
 he trees\, rolling hills\, vineyards\, wildflowers and coastal views. Mary
  is a member of Sky Ranch Gallery in Tomales and is the Featured Artist fo
 r the month of March with her acrylics and watercolors.
LOCATION:Sky Ranch Gallery
URL:https://www.skyranchgallery.com
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Slow Bloom Journey
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T150000
UID:260227jMx1eQZokECcHpk5Xz4L1w
DESCRIPTION:Do you enjoy a slow walk in a valley\, breezes\, wil
 dflowers\, the sounds of songbirds\, the taste of a Douglas Fir
  needle or a California Bay leaf\, the aroma of Tarweed\, or w
 atching wild turkeys and California Quail hunt for seeds and ins
 ects in the grass?  Each month (weather permitting) we will exp
 lore one or two of our accessible trails-- the Creekside Nature
  Trail\, and the Meadow Trail. Suitable for all levels and a r
 ange of mobility\, these Sunday afternoon adventures will accommod
 ate people using walkers or wheelchairs\, young children\, parents
  with babies in strollers\, as well as those who just enjoy sl
 ow walks in nature that stimulate the five senses. Our March ou
 ting will focus on the blooms of Sugarloaf.\n\nTickets are $5 fo
 r adults and free for children under 18 years of age (a parent
  or legal guardian must accompany minors). Meet at the White Ba
 rn parking lot. There will be frequent stops and opportunities f
 or conversation\, photography\, nature journaling\, wildlife viewing
 \, resting\, etc.\, so bring your nature journal\, camera\, or b
 inoculars if you have them. Wear comfortable shoes\, a hat\, sun
  protection\, bring water and if desired\, a snack. Parking fees
  apply. Rain cancel. In the event of rain\, we will reschedule
  to Sunday\, April 12\, at the same time.
LOCATION:Sugarloaf Ridge State Park
URL:https://sec.regfox.com/2026-marjourn
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Glass Menagerie
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T160000
UID:260227UFwlUIKlVk-sc1bYJe2_Og
DESCRIPTION:The 2026 Season at Curtain Call Theatre starts off with **The 
 Glass Menagerie**\, the play that made Tennessee Williams famous.\n\nHave 
 You Ever Felt Stuck Between Your Dreams and Reality? This Play Gets It.\n\
 nImagine being trapped in a tiny apartment during the Great Depression —
  no money\, no way out\, just a family clinging to hopes that may never co
 me true. That's exactly what The Glass Menagerie is about.\n\nWritten by T
 ennessee Williams — one of America's greatest playwrights — this story
  follows a restless son\, an overbearing mom\, and a painfully shy daughte
 r as they each chase dreams that feel just out of reach. It's emotional\, 
 poetic\, and honestly… kind of hits different when you think about your 
 own life.\n\nThis iconic play is literally studied in classrooms worldwide
 \, so seeing it live is like watching your textbook come to life — excep
 t way more powerful.\n\n📅 March 13–29\, 2026\n\n📍 20347 Hwy 116\, 
 Monte Rio\, CA\n\n🎟️ Grab your tickets at russianriverhall.com or cal
 l (707) 387-5072\n\nThe Glass Menagerie by Tennessee Williams is directed 
 by Michael Tabib.\n\nShowing at the Russian River Hall in Monte Rio\, CA f
 rom March 13-29\, 2026.\n\nProgram was made possible\, in part\, with fund
 s from Creative Sonoma and the California Arts Council (CAC).\n\nBy specia
 l arrangement with Dramatists Play Services\, Inc.
LOCATION:Curtain Call Theatre
URL:https://www.russianriverhall.com/2026/02/18/march-13-29-the-glass-mena
 gerie/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"You're My Neighbor" Art Exhibit
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T170000
UID:260227Bly7xFWUtUuTui2i3zKSUg
DESCRIPTION:Come out to Point Reyes and celebrate neighbors!   \n\nFrom 
 mooing cows and soaring birds to friendly faces down the road\, Cedars art
 ists take a joyful look at their Marin County neighborhood. This exhibitio
 n explores all the things that make their corner of the world special—op
 en fields\, wild creatures\, familiar people\, and the everyday moments in
  between. Through colorful\, thoughtful\, and imaginative works\, “You
 ’re My Neighbor” celebrates the beauty of living side by side and shar
 ing a place we call home.\n\n​Cedars “You’re My Neighbor!” art exh
 ibition runs from March 3 through April 12\, 2026
LOCATION:Toby's Feed Barn
URL:https://www.cedarslife.org/events
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:In Her Power
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T160000
UID:260225M2vNpnSKQE6LCN-qdwTYbA
DESCRIPTION:In Her Power\n\nA Collaboration by Priscila Soares & JeanCheri
 e\n\nIn Her Power is a group exhibition celebrating women’s presence\, s
 trength\, and creative expression. Anchored by a collaborative\, life-size
  sculptural work by Priscila Soares and JeanCherie\, the exhibition brings
  together works by women artists exploring power as something lived\, embo
 died\, and deeply personal.\n\nAt the heart of the gallery stands a mounta
 in lioness woman — a guardian figure shaped by two artists working toget
 her\, each bringing her own voice\, materials\, and vision. Surrounding th
 is central work\, invited artists contribute pieces that reflect their own
  relationship to power\, resilience\, intuition\, and selfhood.\n\nRather 
 than offering a single definition\, In Her Power invites viewers to witnes
 s many expressions of strength — quiet and fierce\, ancestral and contem
 porary\, individual and shared. It is both a celebration of women artists 
 and an invitation to step into presence\, creativity\, and connection.\n\n
 Opening Reception:\n\nMarch 1\, 12–4pm\n\nGallery Hours:\n\nSundays in M
 arch\, 12–4pm\n\nLocation:\n\nMare Island Art Studios\n\n110 Pintado St.
 \n\nVallejo\, CA
LOCATION:Mare Island Art Studios
URL:https://mareislandartstudios.com/events/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
