BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:T-Bone N Weasel - Live Theatre
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260329T140000
UID:260219hp03Cnjk40StmK7PpIn2aA
DESCRIPTION:The play follows the antic peregrinations of two ex-convicts a
 s they make their erratic way across South Carolina in search of a hot mea
 l or an easy mark.\n\nHoping to bring themselves up to at least the povert
 y level\, two ex-convicts\, T Bone \\(who is Black\\) and Weasel \\(who is
  White\\) have stolen a rather decrepit Buick and have set off across Sout
 h Carolina with minor mayhem in mind. Moving swiftly from one adventure t
 o another\, they botch an attempted robbery\,  are swindled out of the Bu
 ick by a fast-talking used car dealer\, run afoul of a sexually voracious 
 lady farmer\, fall into the clutches of a larcenous country preacher\, and
  try to make off with the automobile of a politically ambitious small town
  doctor who wants to exhibit them as examples of what poverty can do to pe
 ople. Then it is back on the road again…\n\nEvery time they try to break
  the law\, the law breaks them. A tale of two idiots\, smartly told by pla
 ywright Jon Klein\, “T-Bone n Weasel” is kind of like a good road-kill
 : it’s funny\, gross and makes a lasting impression. — Variety\n\nFeat
 uring:\n\nT-Bone – Aldo Billingslea\n\nWeasel – Timothy Redman\n\nVern
 a Mae – Sylvia Burboeck\n\nSponsored by Linda Hillel & Jon Eisenberg and
  Malin Giddings & Richard Hechler\n\nTheatre - Programmed by Aldo Billings
 lea and Amy Kossow\n\nTHE 222 / 222 Healdsburg Avenue / Healdsburg CA
LOCATION:THE 222 / Healdsburg
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/t-bone-n-weasel-live-th
 eatre/18156402/2026-03-29T14
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Edible & Medicinal Plant Walk
