DESCRIPTION:Travel the World—No Passport Required!\n\nEvery Sunday at 10
 :00 AM\, grab your global one-way ticket to fitness. We’re traveling acr
 oss continents through rhythm and movement\, blending high-energy world da
 nces with a full-body workout. Whether you’re a seasoned pro or have two
  left feet\, come sweat\, smile\, and discover your new favorite beat.\n\n
 Who: All adult ages and skill levels.\n\nWhen: Sundays @ 10:00 AM.\n\nTh
 e Vibe: Pure fun\, global rhythms\, and a community that moves together.\
 n\nAbout Zeena\n\nZeena Quinn’s World Dance classes are based on learnin
 g coordination\, motivating the brain\, dance techniques\, and therefore\,
  mind-body transformation. By creating a supportive system\, participants 
 discover themselves in their own way via dance.\n\nParticipants will work 
 upper and lower body\, cardio and mostly rhythms & coordination. One will 
 understand and learn to identify the different rhythms while having fun! Z
 eena has a lifetime of experience in dance\, professional performance\, ch
 oreography\, teaching\, as well as\, in fitness and resistance training.\n
 \nZeena has toured the Bay Area presenting a variety of American swing\, C
 harlston\, hip hop\, disco\, line dances\, and international dance styles 
 such as Bollywood\, Afro-Brazilian/Samba\, Flamenco\, and European and Eas
 tern Folk. These authentic dance techniques demonstrate how our body is an
  instrument. Because of her extensive range of dance training\, she brings
  the authenticity of technique into her vibrant teaching style.\n\nCome ta
 ke a trip around theworld! Comfortable clothes and worn shoes that tie. No
  Hoka or hiking shoes please.
LOCATION:Salsa Dance Marin
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/world-dance/18336667/20
 26-03-29T10
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
