DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nWednesdays\, April 1 – May 20\, 2026 6:00 PM –
  9:00 PM\n\nLocation\n\nRoom 117\, Ceramics Studio\n\nExperience Level\n\n
 Intermediate and Advanced\n\nEvent Categories: Ceramics\, Extended Classes
 \n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n17\\+\n\n$265 – Registration Cost $30 – Materials Fe
 e $295 – Total Registration Cost\n\nA continuation of our intermediate c
 ourse\, this upper level / advanced course will help you hone your throwin
 g skills in the studio.\n\nAbout the Class\n\nThis session is designed for
  people who have already taken multiple wheel throwing courses. A continua
 tion of our intermediate course\, this upper level / advanced course will 
 help you hone your throwing skills through more complex demos\, and nuance
 d approaches to technical throwing. In this 8 week course\, students will 
 dive deep into developing their own unique voice as they build a technical
  toolset for the independent maker. In addition to throwing\, surface deco
 ration techniques will be explored as well as the opportunity to experimen
 t with different clay bodies. With your 8 week class registration\, studen
 ts receive the opportunity to purchase a studio pass for ½ off during the
  duration of their class. Sign ups for membership will be included in your
  preclass email
