BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Homeschool Day: Snoopy's Family
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260401T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260401T123000
UID:260313XZf1AvskMUWcwk0TUwdHPA
DESCRIPTION:Explore the Museum’s newest exhibition\, Snoopy’s Family\
 , and learn about animals through hands-on activities. Discover what famil
 ies in the animal kingdom look like\, explore animal homes\, and try build
 ing one. Plus\, learn to draw Snoopy and other Peanuts animal characters
 ! Enjoy the optional opportunity to extend the day with ice skating at Sn
 oopy’s Home Ice from 12:30–2:00 pm. Recommended for ages 4-12.\n\nTh
 e event features the following guests and interactive activities:\n\nRead 
 to a therapy dog with Paws as Loving Support \\(PALS\\)\n\nMeet a senior
  dog and learn about adopting older dogs with Brooks Legacy Senior Dog Re
 scue\n\nUnderstand how you can help animals with Memorial Beach Vet Hospi
 tal\n\nDiscover books about animals with the Northwest Regional Santa Ros
 a Library\n\nCreate stories and comics about animals with professional car
 toonists\n\nLearn about bears in California with North Bay Bear Collaborat
 ive\n\nExplore invertebrates with Xerces Society for Invertebrate Conserv
 ation\n\nInvestigate marine mammals with The Marine Mammal Center\n\nand 
 more!\n\nCost:\n\nYouth: $10.00 per child by March 25 \\($15.00/child a
 fter\\). Includes Museum activities only\, no ice skating.\n\nYouth \\+ Ic
 e Skating: $17.00 by March 25 \\($22.00/child after\\)\n\nChaperones: 
 Free with paying child \\(no ice skating\\)\n\nChaperones \\+ Ice Skating:
  $7.00 per person\n\nAll sales are final\; no refunds available. Registrat
 ion is required for all attendees\, including chaperones. Youth and chi
 ldren cannot attend without an adult chaperone. Early registration encour
 aged\, as this event typically sells out.
LOCATION:Charles M. Schulz Museum
URL:https://schulzmuseum.org/homeschool-day-snoopys-family/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
