UID:260325-opVnlkohkubSPiDXZ61tA
DESCRIPTION:MERCY PRESENTS:\n\nLast Mic Standing: Comedy Showdown\n\nBattl
 e for the Main Stage.\n\nOn Friday\, April 3rd from 8PM – 9:30PM\, eight
  fearless comics step into the spotlight for one night of rapid-fire punch
 lines\, crowd reactions\, and high-stakes humor inside The Lounge at Mercy
 .\n\nThis isn’t an open mic.\n\nThis is a showdown.\n\n8 Comics. 3 Judge
 s. Audience Vote.\n\nEach comedian brings their sharpest material and stro
 ngest stage presence to compete for the title of Last Mic Standing. Judges
  score the sets. The crowd weighs in. The energy decides everything.\n\nOn
 e night. One winner.\n\nThe stakes are real. The winner takes home a $100 
 cash prize and earns a paid hosting spot at the next Mercy’s Tokes & Jok
 es Comedy Night. Win the crowd. Own the mic. Come back as host.\n\nComics 
 sign up here & get a free entry to the event: https://bit.ly/lastmicsignup
  Names will be drawn from a hat day of the event.\n\nThis is a 420-friendl
 y comedy competition hosted inside our fully licensed cannabis consumption
  lounge\, where elevated vibes meet elevated punchlines. Guests are welcom
 e to enjoy responsibly while comics go head-to-head under the lights. Grea
 t sets hit different here.\n\nTicket Tiers\n\n$20 — General Admission \\
 (Open Seating\\) Entry to Comedy Showdown 🎤 Open seating \\(first come\
 , first served\\). Come early for the best spot.\n\n$30 — GA \\+ Goodie 
 Bag A little extra ✨ Entry \\+ goodie bag \\($15 value\\) included. Open
  seating \\(first come\, first served\\). \n\n⭐ $40 — Preferred Bucke
 t Seat \\+ Goodie Bag \\(Most Popular\\) Comfort upgrade ⭐ Guaranteed bu
 cket seat \\+ shared table access\, plus goodie bag \\($15 value\\) includ
 ed. Limited seating.\n\n🔥 $135 — Couch Crew Pass \\(3 Guests \\+ Prem
 ium Bag\\) Bring your crew 🔥 Includes admission for 3 guests\, reserved
  couch seating with a dedicated table\, plus premium bag \\($100 value\\) 
 included. Only 11 couches.\n\n21\\+ Only | DCC \\# C12-0000420-LIC
LOCATION:The Lounge at Mercy
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/last-mic-standing-comed
 y-showdown/18359023/2026-04-03T20
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Small Wonders
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260403T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260403T170000
UID:260324weGDJYMKlEC1Z_XMyUeeUQ
DESCRIPTION:Call for Art: Small Wonders\n\nSome of the most exquisite beau
 ty can be captured in the smallest of images and objects: the iridescence 
 of a hummingbird in flight\, a millefiori paperweight\, Faberge eggs\, or 
 a miniature woven basket. These pieces are modest in size but powerful in 
 creativity and expression.\n\nHealdsburg Center for the Arts (HCA) invites
  artists to submit paintings\, original fine art prints\, collage\, mixed 
 media\, drawings\, fiber arts\, sculptures\, ceramics\, and jewelry for th
 is exhibition.\n\nApplication Requirements:\n\n\\- Platform: All applicati
 ons must be submitted via EntryThingy\n\n\\- Eligibility: Work must be ori
 ginal and completed within the past two years. Photos in the application m
 ust represent the actual work intended for exhibition.\n\n\\- Size/Weight:
  Artwork must not exceed 12" x 12" unframed (144 sq in) or 196 sq in frame
 d. Maximum weight is 40 lbs.\n\n\\- Display: 2-D pieces must be securely w
 ired (no alligator clips). 3-D work must be stable\; artists are responsib
 le for on-site assembly if required.\n\n\\- Sales: All work must be for sa
 le. HCA retains a 40% commission\; artists receive 60%. Please list retail
  prices only.\n\nKey Dates:\n\n\\- Entry Deadline: May 10\, 2026 (9 PM)\n\
 n\\- Notification of Selection: By May 13\, 2026\n\n\\- Shipped Work Deadl
 ine: Wednesday\, May 27\, 2026 (must include pre-paid return label)\n\n\\-
  Hand-Delivery: Sunday\, May 31 (12–4 PM) and Monday\, June 1 (11 AM–1
  PM)\n\n\\- Exhibition Dates: June 4\, 2026 – July 19\, 2026\n\n\\- Open
 ing Reception: Saturday\, June 6\, 2026 (4–6 PM)\n\n\\- Pick-up/Return S
 hipping: July 19 (12–4 PM) and July 20 (11 AM–1 PM)\; shipping the wee
