BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wreckless Strangers Live at Papermill Creek Saloon
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260403T203000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260403T203000
UID:260319V_dWdbw2f0O6aymm9pHLYw
DESCRIPTION:Thrilled that their newly released singles are getting nationa
 l radio airplay and moving up the Top 100 Americana Singles and Top 100 AA
 A Singles Charts\,**Wreckless Strangers** continue their album release ce
 lebration with several shows in the San Francisco Bay Area\, including **
 Lucca Bar & Grill** in Benicia\, the newly reopened historic **Papermill 
 Creek Saloon i**n West Marin\, a stint at the **Golden Gate Park Bandshel
 l\,** a fundraiser for **Challenged Athletes Foundation**\, and more.\n\n
 Wreckless Strangers return to their roots with their forthcoming studio al
 bum\,*Dirty Souls*. The six-song collection marks the band’s rawest and 
 most visceral effort to date — a modern take on the arena rock of the 
 ’70s and ’80s that inspired their earliest musical influences. The fir
 st single\, **"Dirty Soul\,"** came out on January 23 and is getting radi
 o play across the nation\, and is available on most streaming platforms. T
 heir second single\, **“The Runaround\,”** was released on February 
 27\, and the full album comes out on March 27. Concert attendees will ha
 ve the opportunity to purchase copies of the CD at the live shows. \n\n**
 *Dirty Souls*** is the band’s third studio outing under the tutelage of
  Grammy-winning producer **Dave Way**\, who fosters a level of depth and 
 organic cohesion that firmly establishes Wreckless Strangers in San Franci
 sco’s storied rock ’n’ roll legacy. The songwriting is among their m
 ost intimate and personal\, exploring themes of relationships\, loss\, emp
 owerment\, and perseverance. Co-lead singers **Amber Morris** and **Davi
 d Noble** function as a single organism\, bringing the songs to life with
  bluesy grit\, soul\, and humanity bolstered by rock-solid\, road-hewn gro
 oves.\n\nVisit **WrecklessStrangers.com** and follow the band on social 
 media for updates.\n\n**Wreckless Stranger**s is a collective of friends a
 nd musicians carrying the torch for San Francisco’s grand rock ‘n’ r
 oll tradition. Their unique blend of “Ameri-Cali Soul” melds the conte
 mporary blues stylings of Bonnie Raitt and Boz Scaggs\; the songwriting se
 nsibilities of Sons of Champlin and Fleetwood Mac\; the swashbuckling Amer
 icana of the Lost Planet Airmen and Peter Rowan\; and the funk of Sly Ston
 e and Tower of Power with a dash of Grateful Dead and Jefferson Airplane f
 or flavor and unpredictability. With soaring vocal harmonies and burning i
 nstrumental improvisation\, framed by concise\, poignant original songwrit
 ing\, Wreckless Strangers seek to honor and carry forth the brand of free-
 spirited musical fun and adventure that defines the Bay Area. \n\nThe ban
 d features **Amber Morris** on lead vocals\; **David Noble** on lead gu
 itar and lead vocals\; **Joshua Zucker** on bass and vocals\; **Mick Hel
 lman** on drums and vocals\; **Rob Anderson** on guitar and vocals\; and
  **Fletcher Nielsen** on keys. \n\nThe band was recently invited back to
  perform live on Nashville’s famed Americana Roots radio station\, WMOT\
 , and performed at NAMM in Southern California in January.
LOCATION:Papermill Creek Saloon
URL:https://papermillcreeksaloon.com/events/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
