BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Lake Solano Park Native Plant Demonstration Garden Tour
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T120000
UID:260325U1LRd4m-vkeXAt1I7s0kLw
DESCRIPTION:Learn about local native plants and their benefits during thi
 s guided Native Plant Demonstration Garden tour at Lake Solano Park! Plan
 ted in early 2025\, this new garden features species that are important fo
 r Putah Creek wildlife and have cultural value. Funded by a grant from th
 e California Coastal Conservancy\, it is a collaborative project between S
 olano Resource Conservation District\, Putah Creek Council\, Solano Count
 y Parks\, and Yocha Dehe Wintun Nation. \n\nThe tour will take place on 
 Saturday\, April 4th from 10AM – 12PM\, led by Maddie Galal\, Putah Cre
 ek Council’s Stewardship Coordinator and Vice President of the Califor
 nia Native Plant Society- Willis L Jepson \\(Solano\\) Chapter. Registrat
 ion is required\, where you will receive detailed directions a few days pr
 ior to the event. \n\nNote that parking at Lake Solano Park is $8 for all
  visitors. This event is open to all ages\, but is best suited for those 
 ages 12 and older. \n\nAll attendees must sign the Putah Creek Council an
 d California Native Plant Society waivers before participating in this eve
 nt. Participants under the age of 18 must have them signed by a parent/gua
 rdian.
LOCATION:Lake Solano County Park
URL:https://putahcreekcouncil.org/event/guided-tour-of-lake-solano-park-na
 tive-plant-demonstration-garden/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:American Red Cross Adult and Pediatric First-Aid/CPR/AED Class (Bl
 ended)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T133000
UID:260325HgCWn5R8NUa7VUvaCUDqvg
DESCRIPTION:Learn how to save a life!\n\nFocusing on recognizing and treat
 ing adults\, children and babies experiencing life-threatening situations 
 in the critical minutes before 911 arrives\, we will cover how to handle c
 hoking\, cardiac arrest\, severe bleeding\, sudden illness\, heart attack\
 , stroke - and more. We'll make sure everyone leaves the class prepared to
  step in and provide help.\n\nThis is a blended class offering the best of
  both worlds: Watch the presentations and related material online at your 
 convenience before heading to the in-person session to practice our skills
  in a small-group setting\, with our friendly and patient instructor answe
 ring questions along the way. Your American Red Cross certificate will be 
 valid for 2 years.\n\n\\(This community class event is held at a branch of
  Sonoma County Library. We thank them for their hospitality. They have req
 uested that we mention that this program is neither sponsored by nor affil
 iated with the Sonoma County Library. Done!\\)\n\nPlease check out our web
 site for more details\, and feel free to get in touch with any questions. 
 Hope to see you there!
LOCATION:Sonoma Valley Library
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/american-red-cross-adul
 t-and-pediatric-first-aid-cpr-aed-class-blended/18227808/2026-04-04T11
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
