BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Senderos: Flora
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T130000
UID:260324LVh7NH2WI0CAkWPx70N1mA
DESCRIPTION:\\[Translated to English below\\]Ven a una caminata donde expl
 oraremos algunas de las plantas originarias en Sugarloaf\, su historia nat
 ural\, herbología y folklore. Tendremos la oportunidad de aprender cómo 
 utilizar la aplicación móvil iNaturalist para ayudarnos a identificar es
 pecímenes que encontremos\, así que cerciórese de que la batería de su
  dispositivo esté 100% cargada. \n\nNos reuniremos en el área de picnic
  enfrente del estacionamiento principal. Recorreremos partes de varios sen
 deros con hábitats variados para un máximo de 3 millas con aproximadamen
 te 200 pies de elevación.\n\nEvento gratuito\; requiere registración. Ha
 y transportación disponible gratuita dentro de un radio de 20 millas al p
 arque para familias que la necesiten. Para detalles y registración\, visi
 ta sec.regfox.com/aves2026\n\nAlternativamente\, llama a Mario (707-387-40
 87)\, Alma (707-247-5767\, entre martes y sábado) o escríbenos a sendero
 s@sonomaecologycenter.org. ¿No puedes acompañarnos ese día? ¡Guarda la
  fecha el 4 de abril para más aventuras!\n\nSenderos Naturales es parcial
 mente respaldado por una beca de Parks California.\n\n\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\
 _\\_\\_\\_\n\nJoin us on a hike where we'll explore some of Sugarloaf 's n
 ative plants \, their natural history \, herbology \, and folklore. We'll 
 have the opportunity to learn how to use the iNaturalist mobile app to hel
 p us identify specimens we find \, so make sure your device 's battery is 
 fully charged . This event is planned around a primarily Latino audience a
 nd will be conducted in Spanish. Families from underrepresented groups are
  welcome to join. Free transportation available within a 20 mile radius of
  the park for families in need. For questions\, please email senderos@sono
 maecologycenter.org.\n\nThis event is partially supported by Route to Park
 s\, a project of Parks California.
LOCATION:Sugarloaf Ridge State Park
URL:https://sec.regfox.com/flora2026
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Chilaquiles and Quekis: A Family Mexican Breakfast Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T120000
UID:260324Asz3EtWmFEyUcmVn4rNjKQ
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nSaturday\, April 4\, 2026 9:00 AM – 12:00 PM\n\n
 Experience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nEvent Categories: Bilingual\, Culinary A
 rts\, Family\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\nAll Ages\n\nFamily Registration \\(Up to 5 m
 embers\\)\n\n$100\n\nMaster Mexican breakfast favorites chilaquiles and qu
 ekis. Learn tortilla techniques\, salsa-making\, and create authentic morn
 ing dishes bursting with flavor.\n\nWhat you’ll do\n\nBring the whole fa
 mily to this hands-on Mexican breakfast workshop\, open to families with c
 hildren of all ages \\(up to 5 members\\). Working together in your own fa
 mily group\, you’ll master two beloved morning classics: chilaquiles and
  quekis. Learn to make authentic chilaquiles from scratch\, including home
 made salsa verde or roja\, perfectly sauced tortilla chips\, and all the t
 oppings\, then dive into quekis\, a fun Mexican breakfast mashup of quesad
 illas and classic morning flavors with golden\, crispy results every time.
  Along the way\, your family will build real confidence with essential Mex
 ican cooking techniques\, from working with fresh and dried chiles to craf
 ting flavorful salsas with the perfect consistency. Whether you’re new t
 o Mexican cuisine or looking to level up your skills together\, you’ll l
 eave with recipes ready to recreate for weekend brunch\, holiday mornings\
 , or any day that deserves a delicious upgrade. Perfect for families who l
 ove to cook\, eat\, and explore bold\, authentic flavors together.
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/chilaquiles-and-quekis/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
