BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Primavera en el Parque - Spring
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T140000
UID:2603193P-wtHlZwEWX0o8zC0K28A
DESCRIPTION:¡Vamos al parque! El sábado 4 de abril te invitamos a celeb
 rar la llegada de la primavera en el Jack London State Historic Park. Como
  en todos nuestros programas de Rutas y Aventuras\, ¡la entrada es comp
 letamente gratuita! Comenzaremos la mañana con unos bocadillos ligeros y
  una caminata por el bosque\, donde platicaremos sobre los cambios que tr
 ae la primavera y lo que ocurre con las plantas en esta época del año. V
 engan listos para aprender y disfrutar del aire libre.\n\n¡Es primavera y
  es fin de semana de Pascua\, así que no olviden traer sus canastas! Al r
 egresar de nuestra caminata\, iniciaremos la gran búsqueda de huevos de P
 ascua para toda la familia. También ofreceremos un almuerzo con arroz\, f
 rijoles\, tacos y bebidas refrescantes. Además\, tendremos una rifa de un
  pase anual y actividades para que explores el parque a tu propio ritmo co
 n amigos y familiares.\n\nCelebrate the arrival of spring at Jack London S
 tate Historic Park with a guided hike in Spanish. As with all “Rutas y A
 venturas” programs\, admission is free \\(registration is required\\). 
  We will start the morning with some light snacks and a walk through the 
 forest\, where we’ll talk about the changes of the season and what happe
 ns with the plants at this time of year.  \n\nIt’s Easter weekend and\,
  upon returning from the walk\, there will be an Easter egg hunt for the w
 hole family\, plus lunch featuring rice\, beans\, tacos\, and refreshing d
 rinks. There will be a raffle for an annual park pass\, along with activit
 ies that allow you to explore the park at your own pace with friends and f
 amily.
LOCATION:Jack London State Historic Park
URL:https://bohemian.com/events-calendar/#/details/primavera-en-el-parque-
 spring/18345636/2026-04-04T09
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Art Exhibit: The Poetic Landscape
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T180000
UID:260318dH5xfW2IX0aS5GIJHaLfaw
DESCRIPTION:Date: FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE  3/13/26\n\n**APRIL EXHIBIT: THE 
 POETIC LANDSCAPE**\n\nEXHIBIT DATES:  March 30  – April 26\, 2026\n\n*
 *RECEPTION: SATURDAY\, APRIL 4\, 2026\, 3-5 pm: Join us to meet KAREN MILL
 ER and PHYLLIS RAPP\;  celebrate the show and enjoy a poetry reading by f
 eatured guest\, Linda Loveland Reid\, gallery artist and published author.
   Be sure to take part in the Gallery’s free monthly drawing for a beau
 tiful work by a Gallery artist.  Refreshments will be served.**\n\nSonoma
  County artist\, **Karen Miller\,** presents **The Poetic Landscape\,** pa
 stel paintings that convey Miller’s personal experience in connecting wi
 th the intrinsic beauty of natural places. In these pieces\, color\, fluid
  shapes and rhythmic design combine to create an uplifting mood – a true
  poetic interlude.  Evoking a happy mood\, “Geyserville Sunflowers\,”
  turning to the sun by nature\, joyfully dance in its luminescence. By the
  river’s edge\, concentric reflections conjure a calm sense of wellbeing
  in “Fetch.”  The viewer feels welcomed by a warm embrace entering a 
 shaded secret spot in “September Trellis.”  Focused on local scenes\,
  these works truly hone in on the stunning landscape out our doors.  Mill
 er remarked “ As I contemplate the very real places of beauty surroundin
 g us\, I try to express my painterly response in hopes it will engender re
 cognition by the viewers.” \n\nMeet the artist: Miller will be hosting 
 the Gallery on March 30\, April 5 & 15 from 11am to 2:30 pm.\n\n The Stai
 rway Smallworks Showcase features **Phyllis Rapp’s Magic Moments\,** a c
 ollection of watercolors that create an atmosphere that is both introspect
 ive and magical.  Familiar domestic scenes are transformed as humans inte
 ract with animals and birds in floral settings.  In “Silent Watcher” 
 the red-headed young woman’s green eyes lock onto ours as she stares ahe
 ad\, flanked by her avian companion.  Experiencing these works is a like 
 taking a mini-step on the wild side\, an exciting and fun experience.\n\nM
 eet the artist: Rapp will be hosting the Gallery on March 30 and April 10 
 from 11am to 6 pm.\n\nAlso join us for **ART NITE HEALDSBURG**\, Thursday\
 , April 2\, 5 – 6 pm.  The theme for the 2026 kickoff event is Bouquets
  to Art.  ART NITE Healdsburg\, held the 1st Thursday of Every Month\, is
  a community event celebrating art and creativity with over 20 galleries p
 articipating.  ArtNiteHealdsburg.com.\n\nUpstairs Art Gallery\, 306 Cente
 r Street\, Healdsburg\, CA 95448. (707) 431-4214.: OPEN DAILY: 11am – 6 
 pm.    **www.upstairsart gallery.net** \n\nFor further information: Con
 tact: Beverly Bird\, Press Contact\, at bvdrio@sonic.net or 707-799-1490.
LOCATION:Upstairs Art Gallery
URL:http://www.upstairsartgallery.net
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Faye Dorman is the Featured Artist for April at Sky Ranch Gallery\
 , Tomales
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T150000
UID:260317BSLJB_SLEkmvbabyCimekA
DESCRIPTION:My oil paintings explore the emotional\, human landscape.\n\nT
 he malleability of oil paint allows her to layer color\, to scrape away an
 d rebuild and to let brushwork remain as a record of the hand and feeling 
 behind it. \n\n   My years of being a therapist and sitting with faces 
 that hold and reflect emotion is what I hope to capture in a portrait. I 
 invite viewers to recognize their own internal world reflected back.
LOCATION:Sky Ranch Gallery
URL:https://www.skyranchgallery.com
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Bottle Baby Breakfast Club
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T160000
UID:260312HYpGsZYuqEaFXtGYRen2zQ
DESCRIPTION:**Tiny Hooves\, Big Hearts: Our Ongoing Rescue Mission**\n\n**
 At Goatlandia\, our mission is simple: to give love\, safety\, and a secon
 d chance to animals who need it most.**\n\n**We were recently called to re
 scue three baby goats. These tiny babies are now safe at Goatlandia\, and 
 they need bottle feeding several times a day to stay healthy and thrive.**
 \n\n**That’s Where You Come In: The Bottle Baby Breakfast Club**\n\n**St
 arting March 6th\, join us for a heartwarming hour on the farm\, bottle-fe
 eding and cuddling our newest rescues while supporting their care.**\n\n**
 Your $250 donation (covers milk and supplies for weeks of feedings) includ
 es admission for up to four guests for a private\, unforgettable visit to 
 Goatlandia.**\n\n**Come share the love\, feel the magic\, and help us give
  these little ones the future they deserve.**
LOCATION:Goatlandia
URL:https://www.goatlandia.org/bottle-babies-breakfast-club
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:It's A Grand Night For Singing - April 4th
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260404T210000
UID:260311LRJriD7p6kS821FF48Kbyw
DESCRIPTION:The beloved Napa Valley concert series **It’s a Grand Night
  for Singing** returns to the **Jarvis Conservatory** on **Saturday\, 
 April 4 at 7:00 PM** with an engaging evening of opera\, musical theater\
 , jazz\, and art song performed by a vibrant mix of returning favorites an
 d exciting new artists.\n\nKnown for its intimate setting and eclectic pro
 grams\, *It’s a Grand Night for Singing* celebrates the storytelling p
 ower of vocal music across genres. This month’s program explores dramati
 c highlights from opera alongside beloved Broadway melodies\, operetta fav
 orites\, and jazz standards.\n\nAs always\, *It’s a Grand Night for Sin
 ging* celebrates both established performers and emerging artists\, offer
 ing audiences an inspiring evening of music in an intimate concert setting
 .
LOCATION:Jarvis Conservatory
URL:https://jarvisconservatory.ticketspice.com/iagnfs-april-4th
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
