BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sonoma Mountain Cemetery Tour April 6
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260406T103000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260406T121500
UID:250330MrltGSYV8kGsvicL_Sbg6A
DESCRIPTION:Who provided 6\,000 gallons of his own wine reserves to squelc
 h the big fire of 1911 on East 1st Street? Who was pals with Jack and Char
 mian London and received birthday cards from several past and present U.S.
  presidents on her 100th birthday? Who created a whole new industry \\(not
  wine!\\) that brought thousands of tourists and dollars to the Sonoma Val
 ley?\n\n Learn about these and more personalities interned at the City of
  Sonoma Mountain Cemetery when the Sonoma Valley Historical Society \\(SVH
 S\\) inaugurates the Mountain Cemetery Tour on Sunday\, April 6\, 2025. To
 ur groups of 10-15 will be staggered from mid-morning to early afternoon. 
 The groups will start the tour at the Mountain Cemetery water fountain \\(
 look for signs upon arrival\\). Parking available in the Overlook Trail an
 d Veterans Memorial Building parking lots or on 1st Street West.\n\n The 
 cemetery is situated on the western slope of Schocken Hill and will theref
 ore require tour guests to be capable of walking on steep terrain\, wearin
 g suitable walking/hiking footwear\, bringing drinking water\, and a walki
 ng stick \\(optional\\). The tour will last approximately one hour and fif
 teen minutes.\n\n Cost: $20 plus fees. Space is limited\; first come firs
 t served. There will be 3 groups at 10 minute intervals starting at 10:30 
 am To register for the tour\n\nhttps://www.eventbrite.com/e/sonoma-mountai
 n-cemetery-tour-tickets-1289131730709?aff=oddtdtcreator \n\nInquiries abo
 ut the tour can be made at: info@sonomavalleyhistory.org.\n\nSVHS is a 501
 \\(c\\)\\(3\\) non-profit corporation whose mission is collecting\, preser
 ving and sharing the story of our community as told by many voices through
 out Sonoma Valley history.… Please visit our website at: www.sonomavalle
 yhistory.org .
LOCATION:Sonoma Mountain Cemetery
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/sonoma-mountain-cemetery-tour-tickets-128
 9131730709?aff=oddtdtcreator 
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
