SUMMARY:Introduction to Printmaking Spring Session
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260407T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260407T193000
UID:2602162DREgzyB70W9mtEwYvpLVA
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nTuesdays\, March 31 – April 28\, 2026 5:30 Pm 
 – 7:30 PM\n\nExperience Level\n\nBeginning\n\nPrintmaking\n\nAge\\(s\\)\
 n\n16\\+\n\n$195 – Registration Cost $30 – Materials Fee $225 – Tota
 l Registration CostWhat exactly is printmaking? We invite you into our pri
 nt studio to experience a beginner’s journey through this incredible art
  form\n\nWhat you’ll do\n\nWhat is printmaking? We invite you into our p
 rint studio to experience a fun beginner’s journey through this incredib
 le art form in five paced weeks. Join Kelly in this unique introduction to
  print through the world of monotype\, relief\, intaglio and stencil scree
 nprinting. This popular multi-session workshop is only taught twice per ye
 ar in the spring and fall seasons. Students will try various techniques in
  this guided\, hands-on class to create a beginning portfolio of prints. L
 earn a basic understanding of the four classic methods within the family o
 f printmaking and gain access to our member’s print studio to continue w
 orking on your own projects. This class is perfect for absolute beginners 
 or even experienced artists who may need a refresher course in printmaking
 . \n\nMonotype – Create a single print on a flat matrix using ink and a
  variety of marks and  textures\n\nRelief – Carve\, ink and block print
  using a mini speedy carve block and a linocut tool\n\nIntaglio – Draw\,
  scratch and ink onto a surface to roll out a creative print using a small
  press\n\nStencil – Pull a silkscreen and learn to transfer a flat stenc
 il to make a colorful printed impression\n\nNo prior printmaking experienc
 e is necessary. This class requires hand dexterity to maneuver carving too
 ls and studio equipment. Students must feel comfortable handling machinery
 .\n\nMembership has its benefits\n\nAll Silver Memberships and above recei
 ve 10% off the registration cost for any class purchase over $40. Material
 s fees are not discounted.\n\nBecome a member today and find community\, c
 onnection\, and creativity.
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/introduction-to-printmaking
 -spring-session/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
