BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Morning Yoga
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260408T083000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260408T094000
UID:260302qAxf7KjS6kmYQBIDnNN87A
DESCRIPTION:Regenerative Ayurvedic Yoga with Tirza Dawn Come\, step onto y
 our mat with an open heart and an open mind. Invest in your self care and 
 join us for morning yoga in the OCA studio. $20 per class\, $15 for OCA me
 mbers. Each Wednesday from 9:00-10:15 AM in our Studio. Pay at the door fo
 r a-la-carte sessions or use the links below to pay ahead for four weeks a
 t a time.  Pay Online 4 sessions - OCA members  Pay Online 4 sessions - no
 n members Tirza Dawn Naramore is a yogi\, mother\, artist\, ceremonialist 
 and lover of life. She has been practicing and teaching yoga and meditatio
 n for 30 years and offers yoga retreats and trainings that center on optim
 um health\, self realization and self love. Her teachers are from many yog
 a and tantric traditions\, but her primary lineages are Iyengar and Kali R
 ay.  Tirza is deeply devoted to community building and is honored to have 
 created a number of community supported non profits including Mystic Famil
 y Circus and The AWAKEN Project\, which serves families with children on t
 he autism spectrum. Tirza is proud to be the mother of 3 wild teenagers\, 
 including her incredible son who is diagnosed with autism. Tirza's spiritu
 ality is one of many influences and teachings. Beginning with a Christian 
 up-bringing and being raised on a Christian commune in her early childhood
 \, she later expanded into more earth-based ways. While in her 20's Tirza 
 was adopted into the Native American Church\, where she learned from her r
 elatives a way of living the "Beauty Way." During the 1990's and early 200
 0's\, Tirza lived in San Francisco\, Oakland and Berkeley\, directing the 
 Mystic Family Circus\, which was a performance group dedicated to cultural
  awareness and bridge building. She worked with Cirque du Soleil\, Burning
  Man\, Reclaiming\, Contraband\, CELLspace and other Bay Area art collecti
 ves and non profits to provide conscious entertainment and "prayerformance
 s" for the betterment of humankind and the planet. In 2012\, Tirza helped 
 to found the Buckeye Gathering\, an ancestral skills gathering in Northern
  California which draws teachers and students of all ages to learn ancestr
 al ways of tending the earth and survival skills. Tirza Dawn was the found
 er of yoga programming and the Ayurvedic Yoga Teacher Trainings at the dhy
 ana Center of Ayurveda in Sebastopol\, California\, which operated a commu
 nity center of healing and education from 2010 to 2020.
LOCATION:Occidental Center for the Arts
URL:https://www.occidentalcenterforthearts.org/upcoming-events/ew6dc3w3s87
 emgn-f7ghs-2rk62
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Art Of Acrylics
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260408T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260408T120000
UID:260210aUYtBhWSmUqrcvMS9SRuYw
DESCRIPTION:Suzanne will demonstrate each week as students follow along wi
 th weekly painting projects\, exploring techniques such as layering thick 
 and thin paint\, using gels and palette knife\, and applying color theorie
 s. Students can work on their own projects as well. Whether you're a begin
 ner or looking to refine your skills\, this class covers everything you ne
 ed to know. You'll get informed instruction on how to begin a piece\, from
  choosing the right materials to selecting the perfect color palette. We'l
 l dive into composition techniques to help you craft a balanced\, captivat
 ing piece\, and walk you through the finishing touches that bring your wor
 k to life. Suzanne's artwork ranges from portraits\, figurative genre\, la
 ndscapes and caricatures. She has exhibited in juried shows including The 
 Society of Illustrators in New York and for 10 years at the Southern Calif
 ornia Laguna Beach Art Festival. She has taught classes and workshops for 
 many years and led lecture-demos at art associations from California to Wa
 shington State. For enrollment and supply list\, please text or call Suzan
 ne Carson at 707 888 2083
LOCATION:Datoire Foundation
URL:https://creativesonoma.org/event/the-art-of-acrylics/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
