SUMMARY:Emmet Cohen presents: Miles and Coltrane at 100
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260410T193000
UID:250807sqSw1NT0dUOTxSpM2gm-WQ
DESCRIPTION:In celebration of the centennial of John Coltrane and Miles Da
 vis\, pianist Emmet Cohen brings together an all-star quintet to explore t
 he fundamental questions that shaped their artistry: Why are we here? What
  are we reaching for? Where does the music take us?\n\nA dynamic ensemble 
 led by pianist Emmet Cohen\, featuring saxophonist Tivon Pennicott and tru
 mpeter Jeremy Pelt will celebrate these geniuses in Miles and Coltrane at 
 100.\n\nGuided by the spirit of the infinite\, Cohen continues the journey
  set forth by the architects of jazz — seeking deeper truths through sou
 nd.\n\nA dedicated champion of the musical community\, Cohen believes in j
 azz as a living\, evolving conversation — one that unites people across 
 time and place.\n\nJoin Cohen and his ensemble for a bold\, reimagined exp
 erience of the music that forever changed the course of jazz.\n\nSupported
  in part by Oliver's Markets and Balletto Vineyards
LOCATION:Green Music Center
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/1683717518985507/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
