BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:42nd Street\, a classic Broadway musical presented by Solano Colle
 ge Theatre
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T220000
UID:260325O5gkx-NtP02mFMhuM8HbZw
DESCRIPTION:Solano College Theatre presents\n\n42nd Street\n\n📆April 10
 -26\, 2026\n\n📌4000 Suisun Valley Road\, Fairfield CA\n\n🎟 Tickets: 
 www.solanocollegetheatre.org\n\n📞 \\(707\\) 864-7100\n\n42nd Street cel
 ebrates Broadway\, Times Square and the magic of show biz with wit\, humor
 \, pizzazz\, and a whole lot of TAP DANCING! Come be stunned by color\, wh
 imsy\, dancing\, singing\, and starpower!\n\nCome and meet those dancing f
 eet! 👯 “42nd Street” is coming to Solano County this April!\n\nAbou
 t the show: 42nd Street celebrates Broadway\, Times Square and the magic o
 f show biz with wit\, humor\, and pizzazz. At the height of the Great Depr
 ession\, aspiring chorus girl Peggy Sawyer comes to the big city from Alle
 ntown PA\, and soon lands her first big job in the ensemble of a glitzy ne
 w Broadway show. But just before opening night\, the leading lady breaks h
 er ankle. Will Peggy be able to step in and become a star?\n\nTickets $10-
 $24 online\, by phone\, or at the door!\n\nFri. 4/10 at 7:30 pm \\(opening
  night reception after the show!\\)\n\nSat. 4/11 at 7:30 pm\n\nSun. 4/12 a
 t 2 pm\n\nFri. 4/17 at 10 am \\(Student Matinee\, all welcome!\\)\n\nFri. 
 4/17 at 7:30 pm\n\nSat. 4/18 at 7:30 pm\n\nSun. 4/19 at 2 pm\n\nThurs. 4/2
 3 at 7:30 pm \\(Pay-what-you-can night!\\)\n\nFri. 4/24 at 7:30 pm \\(ASL 
 Interpretation provided\\)\n\nSat. 4/25 at 7:30 pm\n\nSun. 4/26 at 2 pm \\
 (closing show!\\)\n\nAbout the producer: Solano College Theatre is dedicat
 ed to providing quality theatre arts education to the next generation of t
 heatre professionals and producing shows that contribute meaningfully to t
 he culture and entertainment of our Solano County community.
LOCATION:Solano College Theatre
URL:https://www.solanocollegetheatre.org/42nd-street
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
