DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T160000
UID:260319EpHhxLL70EuWMV4BBaCNJA
DESCRIPTION:An Afternoon of Cinematic Poetry and Poetic Spoken Word!\n\nA 
 Stage for Voices. A Screen for Poetry. Discover the magic of the Monologue
 s & Poetry International Film Fest\, an unforgettable experience blending 
 film and poetry that will leave you ready to write your own story.\n\nJoin
  the in-person experience on Saturday\, April 11th\, 2026\, at the Vallejo
  Naval and Historical Museum\, 734 Marin St\, Vallejo\, CA. 1:00-4:00 PM\,
  for a limited screening and poetry open mic.\n\nIn addition\, a Virtual O
 n-Demand Screening will be available from April 12th to April 17th\, featu
 ring all of our Official Selections from around the globe to watch at your
  leisure.\n\nRegistration will provide access to both the Live Screening a
 nd Open Mic\, as well as the Virtual Screening Links\, which will be email
 ed to all registered participants 24 hours prior to the live event and vir
 tual screening week.
LOCATION:Vallejo Naval and Historical Museum
