UID:2603113TPSImiyDES0rQcVK2USzQ
DESCRIPTION:Dan Perlman is a comedian\, writer\, and director from New Yor
 k City. He co-created\, wrote\, and starred in Showtime’s critically-acc
 laimed comedy series\, Flatbush Misdemeanors. Dan made his directorial deb
 ut in the Flatbush episode\, “boomerang\,” which Vulture praised for i
 ts “masterful direction.” Dan also wrote and directed the award-winnin
 g short films\, Cramming and Practice Space.\n\nDan first co-created the p
 rize-winning digital series of Flatbush\, which served as the foundation f
 or the Showtime show. Made on zero-budget\, the first installment became O
 scar-qualified after winning Grand Jury Awards in its film festival run.\n
 \nAs a stand-up\, Dan has been featured on Comedy Central and was named on
 e of the New Faces at the Montreal Just For Laughs Festival. His debut alb
 um\, Emergency Contact\, is a staple on SiriusXM. Dan is a regular at the 
 Comedy Cellar in NYC and headlines venues across the country. His writing 
 has also appeared in The New Yorker.
LOCATION:Sebastopol Center for the Arts
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107860475?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
