BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Classical Impressions: Music of the Fin de Siècle
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T180000
UID:260129Im5olzN6kkKmBF8M7ZmBgw
DESCRIPTION:Recently formed in San Francisco\, the Alora Quartet is dedica
 ted to timeless beauty and connection through music. With a focus on trans
 ition\, reflection\, and momentum\, the quartet brings each piece to life 
 through its exploration of musical storytelling and resonance. Under the m
 entorship of Wonhee Bae and Yeeun Heo\, first violinist and cellist of the
  Esmé Quartet\, the Alora Quartet brings a fresh perspective to the strin
 g quartet tradition\, blending both tradition and innovation.\n\nThe name 
 ‘Alora’ is derived from the Italian word ‘allora’\, meaning ‘the
 n’ or ‘so’\, symbolizing the quartet’s evolving musical journey. T
 he Alora Quartet has had the privilege of working with world-renowned viol
 ist and pedagogue Kim Kashkashian in a masterclass\, an experience that ha
 s influenced their artistic development. The Alora Quartet was founded by 
 violinists Cuna Kim and Qicong Ma\, violist Phoebee Lee\, and cellist Dani
 ela Gonzales Siu.
LOCATION:Haraszthy Villa at Bartholomew Winery
URL:https://musicinplace.org/event/classical-impressions-music-of-the-fin-
 de-siecle/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
