DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T150000
UID:260325isDeanx6PUm6tDEHF0oMyw
DESCRIPTION:Join us in creating animalicious artworks through hands-on act
 ivities that focus on beasties\, inspired by the work of Maija Peeples-Bri
 ght! Irma Rodriguez from RAIZES Collective leads us into the magical world
  of alebrijes\, a tradition of creating hybrid animals rooted in Mexico. E
 xplore animal anatomy with Julia Megna from the Sonoma Ecology Center by l
 ooking at real animal skulls and designing and embellishing your own color
 ful animal head sculpture. Dive into the wonder of collage and the power o
 f patterns with artist Thailan When\, making artworks inspired by the anim
 als of the Chinese Zodiac. ViVO Youth Orchestra performs at 1pm! Saturday\
 , April 11\, 11 – 3 PM Free admission all ages! Registration is requeste
 d. Artwork by Thailan When
LOCATION:Sonoma Valley Museum of Art
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/1868347700487605/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
