BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:42nd Street\, a classic Broadway musical presented by Solano Colle
 ge Theatre
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260412T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260412T163000
UID:260325PK-RORJ0W0mUyaILtln4Kg
DESCRIPTION:Solano College Theatre presents\n\n42nd Street\n\n📆April 10
 -26\, 2026\n\n📌4000 Suisun Valley Road\, Fairfield CA\n\n🎟 Tickets: 
 www.solanocollegetheatre.org\n\n📞 \\(707\\) 864-7100\n\n42nd Street cel
 ebrates Broadway\, Times Square and the magic of show biz with wit\, humor
 \, pizzazz\, and a whole lot of TAP DANCING! Come be stunned by color\, wh
 imsy\, dancing\, singing\, and starpower!\n\nCome and meet those dancing f
 eet! 👯 “42nd Street” is coming to Solano County this April!\n\nAbou
 t the show: 42nd Street celebrates Broadway\, Times Square and the magic o
 f show biz with wit\, humor\, and pizzazz. At the height of the Great Depr
 ession\, aspiring chorus girl Peggy Sawyer comes to the big city from Alle
 ntown PA\, and soon lands her first big job in the ensemble of a glitzy ne
 w Broadway show. But just before opening night\, the leading lady breaks h
 er ankle. Will Peggy be able to step in and become a star?\n\nTickets $10-
 $24 online\, by phone\, or at the door!\n\nFri. 4/10 at 7:30 pm \\(opening
  night reception after the show!\\)\n\nSat. 4/11 at 7:30 pm\n\nSun. 4/12 a
 t 2 pm\n\nFri. 4/17 at 10 am \\(Student Matinee\, all welcome!\\)\n\nFri. 
 4/17 at 7:30 pm\n\nSat. 4/18 at 7:30 pm\n\nSun. 4/19 at 2 pm\n\nThurs. 4/2
 3 at 7:30 pm \\(Pay-what-you-can night!\\)\n\nFri. 4/24 at 7:30 pm \\(ASL 
 Interpretation provided\\)\n\nSat. 4/25 at 7:30 pm\n\nSun. 4/26 at 2 pm \\
 (closing show!\\)\n\nAbout the producer: Solano College Theatre is dedicat
 ed to providing quality theatre arts education to the next generation of t
 heatre professionals and producing shows that contribute meaningfully to t
 he culture and entertainment of our Solano County community.
LOCATION:Solano College Theatre
URL:https://www.solanocollegetheatre.org/42nd-street
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Small Wonders
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260412T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260412T170000
UID:260324sJrBnGf4jk2FY_GvC295Og
DESCRIPTION:Call for Art: Small Wonders\n\nSome of the most exquisite beau
 ty can be captured in the smallest of images and objects: the iridescence 
 of a hummingbird in flight\, a millefiori paperweight\, Faberge eggs\, or 
 a miniature woven basket. These pieces are modest in size but powerful in 
 creativity and expression.\n\nHealdsburg Center for the Arts (HCA) invites
  artists to submit paintings\, original fine art prints\, collage\, mixed 
 media\, drawings\, fiber arts\, sculptures\, ceramics\, and jewelry for th
 is exhibition.\n\nApplication Requirements:\n\n\\- Platform: All applicati
 ons must be submitted via EntryThingy\n\n\\- Eligibility: Work must be ori
 ginal and completed within the past two years. Photos in the application m
 ust represent the actual work intended for exhibition.\n\n\\- Size/Weight:
  Artwork must not exceed 12" x 12" unframed (144 sq in) or 196 sq in frame
 d. Maximum weight is 40 lbs.\n\n\\- Display: 2-D pieces must be securely w
 ired (no alligator clips). 3-D work must be stable\; artists are responsib
 le for on-site assembly if required.\n\n\\- Sales: All work must be for sa
 le. HCA retains a 40% commission\; artists receive 60%. Please list retail
  prices only.\n\nKey Dates:\n\n\\- Entry Deadline: May 10\, 2026 (9 PM)\n\
 n\\- Notification of Selection: By May 13\, 2026\n\n\\- Shipped Work Deadl
 ine: Wednesday\, May 27\, 2026 (must include pre-paid return label)\n\n\\-
  Hand-Delivery: Sunday\, May 31 (12–4 PM) and Monday\, June 1 (11 AM–1
  PM)\n\n\\- Exhibition Dates: June 4\, 2026 – July 19\, 2026\n\n\\- Open
 ing Reception: Saturday\, June 6\, 2026 (4–6 PM)\n\n\\- Pick-up/Return S
 hipping: July 19 (12–4 PM) and July 20 (11 AM–1 PM)\; shipping the wee
 k of July 20.\n\nEntry Fees:\n\n\\- Non-Members: $50 (1 entry)\, $55 (2 en
 tries)\, $60 (3 entries). Includes a $60 yearly supporter membership.\n\n\
 \- Current Members: $40 (1 entry)\, $45 (2 entries)\, $50 (3 entries).
LOCATION:Healdsburg Center for the Arts
URL:https://healdsburgcenterforthearts.org/small-wonders-2/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
