BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:In Conversation with Inez Storer
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260412T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260412T170000
UID:260325YrL7evyXtkOzgkoncdh82g
DESCRIPTION:Sunday\, April 12\, 4:00-5:00pm$15 members\; $20 non-members\n
 \nAn afternoon conversation about Inez's approach to artmaking\, her famil
 y history and the stories that inform her art. There will be time for ques
 tions. \n\nStorer lives in Inverness\, California\, and has a studio in Po
 int Reyes Station. Born in Santa Monica in 1933 to a Catholic father and J
 ewish mother\, she spent time on Hollywood movie sets where her father wor
 ked as an art director. Influenced by stage design\, her work often create
 s a sense of &ldquo\;theatrical space&rdquo\; and reflects her ancestry. S
 hortly before her death\, her mother revealed that she had fled Germany to
  escape Nazism. Storer later learned of cousins who escaped on the Kindert
 ransport. The frustration of being kept from the truth has infused her wor
 k with a distinct angst. Her work is held in many collections including th
 e Jewish Museum in New York\, Manetti Shrem Museum of Art at UC Davis\, Oa
 kland Museum of Art \, the de Young Museum\, San Jos&eacute\; Museum of Ar
 t\, Monterey Museum of Art\, Missoula Museum of Art\, and the National Mus
 eum of American Jewish History.
LOCATION:Petaluma Arts Center
URL:https://mynorthbaytickets.ticketsauce.com/e/in-conversation-with-inez-
 storer?aff=cityspark
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Hook and Ladder Vineyards and Winery
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260412T123000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260412T123000
UID:251219EOGkQ1mVxU6cYvTK5AZoXg
DESCRIPTION:Callie Watts is a singer/songwriter from Northern California w
 ho was raised on classical music\, The Beatles and The Beach Boys before d
 iscovering Joni Mitchell\, Elton John\, Stevie Wonder\, Paul Simon\, Billy
  Joel\, Carole King\, and all the great writers of the ’60s and 70’s w
 ho have influenced her sound and writing style. After graduating high scho
 ol\, Callie began playing and performing solo\, as well as in local and ba
 y area bands of different genres. She’s played blues with Eric Lindell a
 nd the Reds\, funky soul with Phatty\, and jazz/swing with Savoy Swingers 
 along with many other various projects. Callie has taken turns throughout 
 her career as a keyboardist\, guitarist\, writer\, and lead/backing vocali
 st\, and she’s currently a member of the dynamic Sonoma County funk rock
  band Burrows and Dilbeck\, having joined in 2010 as part of the former ba
 nd Frobeck. Over time\, she’s had the honor of opening for acts such as 
 Bootsy Collins\, Elvin Bishop\, Huey Lewis and The News\, War\, Ozomatli\,
  Bill Champlin\, Booker T\, and the B52s. Callie continues to perform freq
 uently as an acoustic solo artist\, focusing on developing a core audience
  and a buzz for her original material. Come hang out and listen at venues 
 such as Aroma Roasters\, Rincon Valley Tap Room and Bottle Shop\, and Hopm
 onk Tavern.
LOCATION:Hook & Ladder Vineyards & Winery
URL:https://www.bandsintown.com/e/107647215?app_id=pkvts0on0m&came_from=28
 7&utm_medium=api&utm_source=partner_api&utm_campaign=event
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
