BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Abstract Collage Minis - Create a Series
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T150000
UID:260324BTMdwtttsE-kzuZ6xiW18A
DESCRIPTION:Schedule\n\nSunday\, April 19\, 2026 11:00 AM – 3:00 PM\n\nL
 ocation\n\nRoom 110\n\nExperience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nEvent Categories:
  Drawing & Painting\, Workshops\n\nAge\\(s\\)\n\n16\\+\n\nRegistration Cos
 t:\n\n$115\n\nMaterials Fee:\n\n$10\n\nTotal Registration Cost:\n\n$125\n\
 nIn this workshop\, French-American collage artist Catherine Cruz guides y
 ou in creating a cohesive series of abstract collages on four wood panels\
 , exploring color\, line\, shape\, design principles\, and paper-mounting 
 techniques.\n\nAbout the Class\n\nIn this workshop\, French-American colla
 ge artist Catherine Cruz will teach you how to create a dynamic series of 
 abstract collages using elements such as color\, line and shape. You will 
 work on four small wood panels to compose a cohesive series. Working on se
 veral panels at once offers several advantages\, including greater creativ
 e momentum\, the ability to build a strong thematic connection between pie
 ces\, and a way to maintain creative flow. This technique allows for a dee
 per exploration of an idea or theme than is possible with a single piece. 
 We will start with short composition exercises to discuss design principle
 s and abstraction. Then Catherine will demonstrate her method for mounting
  papers on the panels. You will have ample time to select papers and creat
 e your designs. We will take a short break for lunch between 12:30 and 1:0
 0 pm so please bring your lunch and a beverage. What you’ll learn from t
 his workshop:\n\nReliable method for layering collage papers\n\nCreative w
 ays to explore abstraction\n\nTechniques for creating a cohesive series\n\
 nStrategies for refining your composition\n\nIMPORTANT: Each participant m
 ust purchase and bring four 6”x6” cradled wood panels to the workshop.
  Instructions for where to purchase your panels and how to prepare them wi
 ll be provided upon registration.\n\nInstructor will provide: a wide assor
 tment of painted and printed collage papers\, brushes\, acrylic medium\, s
 cissors\, rulers.
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://sonomacommunitycenter.org/programs/abstract-collage-minis/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
